---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Scenic road between Nice, Èze and Monaco | Guide";
const description = "English guide to enjoy the scenic roads between Nice, Èze and Monaco, with ideas for simple photo stops and viewpoints.";
const canonical = "/en/guide-scenic-road-nice-eze-monaco.html";
---

<BaseLayout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
  currentPage="guide-scenic-road-nice-eze-monaco"
  canonical={canonical}
>

    <nav class="breadcrumbs container" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/en/">Home</a> › <a href="/en/guides">VTC Guides</a> › <span>Scenic road Nice – Èze – Monaco</span>
    </nav>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow">Scenic drive guide</div>
          <h1 class="section-title">Scenic road between Nice, Èze and Monaco</h1>
          <p>The coastline between Nice and Monaco can be explored using several roads at different heights, each with its own atmosphere and viewpoints.</p>
        </div>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Different types of roads</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Lower coastal road: close to the sea and beaches.</li>
            <li>Middle road: a mix of sea views and village access.</li>
            <li>Higher road: wider views over the coast and the hills.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Ideas for simple stops</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Short photo stops at safe viewpoints.</li>
            <li>A walk through a village on the way.</li>
            <li>A coffee or drink with a view before continuing.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" style="padding-top:1.5rem">
          <h2>Driving or using a private driver</h2>
          <p>You can explore this area with a rental car, public transport or a private driver. If you prefer to focus on the views and stops, a driver can take care of the route and parking.</p>
          <p>To book such a drive, you can note your preferred type of road and number of hours in the <a href="/reservation">booking form</a>.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  
</BaseLayout>
